{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise Yah, for it is good to sing praises to our God;"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "for it is pleasant and fitting to praise him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh builds up Jerusalem. He gathers together the outcasts of Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He heals the broken in heart, and binds up their wounds."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He counts the number of the stars. He calls them all by their names."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Great is our Lord, and mighty in power. His understanding is infinite."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh upholds the humble. He brings the wicked down to the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Sing to Yahweh with thanksgiving. Sing praises on the harp to our God,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who covers the sky with clouds, who prepares rain for the earth,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "who makes grass grow on the mountains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He provides food for the livestock, and for the young ravens when they call."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He doesn’t delight in the strength of the horse. He takes no pleasure in the legs of a man."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh takes pleasure in those who fear him, in those who hope in his loving kindness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Praise Yahweh, Jerusalem! Praise your God, Zion!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For he has strengthened the bars of your gates. He has blessed your children within you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He makes peace in your borders. He fills you with the finest of the wheat."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sends out his commandment to the earth. His word runs very swiftly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He gives snow like wool, and scatters frost like ashes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He hurls down his hail like pebbles. Who can st and before his cold?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sends out his word, and melts them. He causes his wind to blow, and the waters flow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He shows his word to Jacob, his statutes and his ordinances to Israel."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has not done this for just any nation. They don’t know his ordinances. Praise Yah!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}